{{Infobox scientist |name = Amanda Reid |birth_date = |birth_place = |residence = |nationality = Australian |fields = [[Malacology]] |workplaces = [[Australian Museum]] |education = [[Macquarie University]] }} '''Amanda "Mandy" Reid''' is an Australian [[malacologist]] who works as a departmental collection manager at the [[Australian Museum]]. She is a published researcher and author. Her work in taxonomy has resulted in the description of many species of [[velvet worm]]s and [[cephalopod]]s.
==Career== Reid is a graduate of [[Macquarie University]], where she obtained a science degree in 1984, completed a Masters in 1990 and went on to complete a PhD in 1996. She has a particular interest in cephalopods, including [[cuttlefish]] and [[bobtail squid]]s. In 2000, she co-authored the book ''A Guide to Squid, Cuttlefish and Octopuses of Australasia'' with [[Mark Norman (marine biologist)|Mark Norman]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gould.org.au/product/a-guide-to-squid-cuttlefish-and-octopuses-of-australasia/|title=A Guide to Squid, Cuttlefish and Octopuses of Australasia {{!}} Gould League|website=gould.org.au|access-date=2016-05-01}}</ref> Reid has also previously studied velvet worms. Her work has been published in a number of scientific journals, including ''Invertebrate Taxonomy'', ''[[Bulletin of Marine Science]]'', ''Australian Natural History'', ''[[Zootaxa]]'' and others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://australianmuseum.net.au/uploads/documents/19531/reid%20publications%20to%202010.pdf|title=Publications to 2010|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Australian Museum|access-date=2016-05-01}}</ref> Species described by Reid include ''[[Sepia tanybracheia]]'', ''[[Sepia koilados]]'' (2000) and Ken's cuttlefish (''[[Sepia grahami]]'') (2001).<ref>https://www.uow.edu.au/content/groups/public/@web/@health/documents/doc/uow056685.pdf</ref> Reid is member of the Society of Editors (NSW) and [[Sustainable Population Australia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://australianmuseum.net.au/staff/mandy-reid|title=Mandy Reid - Australian Museum|website=australianmuseum.net.au|access-date=2016-05-01}}</ref>
