'''Böhnecke Glacier''' ({{Coord|72|23|S|61|25|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a steep [[glacier]] {{convert|3|nmi|km|0}} wide, which flows southeast to the northwest side of [[Violante Inlet]], on the east coast of [[Palmer Land]]. It was discovered and photographed from the air in December 1940 by members of the [[United States Antarctic Service]]. During 1947 the glacier was photographed from the air by members of the [[Ronne Antarctic Research Expedition]] under [[Finn Ronne]], who in conjunction with the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] (FIDS) charted it from the ground. It was named by FIDS for [[Gunther Böhnecke]], a German oceanographer and a member of the German expedition in the ''Meteor'', 1925–27.<ref name=gnis/>

