'''Elise Hofmann''' (February 5, 1889 – March 14, 1955 ) was an Austrian [[paleobotanist]] and [[geologist]]. Born in [[Vienna]], she graduated from the [[University of Vienna]] in 1920. She produced over 120 works, including the 1934 book ''Palaeohistologie der Pflanze'' (''Paleohistology of the Plant''). She was made correspondent of the [[Geological Survey of Austria]] in 1931 and the {{Interlanguage link multi|Landesmuseum Niederösterreich|de}} in 1933.<ref name="Haines2001">{{cite book|first=Catharine M. C.|last= Haines|title=International Women in Science: A Biographical Dictionary to 1950|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HftdjMNDvwIC&pg=PR137|year=2001|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-57607-090-1|page=137}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=Kurt|last= Ehrenberg|title= Elise Hofmann|journal=Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien|volume=96|year= 1956|pages=5–6| language=German|url=http://www.zobodat.at/biografien/Hofmann_Elise_1.PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=O.|last= Kühn|year=1956|title= Elise Hofmann|journal=Mitteilungen der Geologischen Gesellschaft in Wien|volume= 49|pages=357–363|language=German|url=http://www.zobodat.at/biografien/Hofmann_Elise_MittGeolGes_049_357-364.pdf}}</ref> {{botanist|E.Hofm.|inline=y}}

